{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cfe76a44-e41d-4a2a-a84b-42daa25420dc","content":"\n\n**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped VSTest as the default runner.**\n\nIn 3.x the SDK still wired up the VSTest adapter, so `vstest.console` could discover tests. Starting with 4.0, the default runner is **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the \"MSTest runner\"), which produces a standalone executable — not a VSTest-compatible assembly. That's why `vstest.console` sees zero tests.\n\n### Fix options\n\n**Option A – Restore VSTest mode** (minimal CI change):\nAdd this to your `.csproj` / `Directory.Build.props`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Option B – Adopt the new platform** (recommended long-term):\nReplace `vstest.console` in your pipeline with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test          # .NET 9+ understands the new platform natively\n# or run the test exe directly:\n./YourTests --report-trx\n```\n\nOption B is the direction Microsoft is pushing; the new platform is faster and supports parallel execution out of the box.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"298a4237-a165-4c0b-b250-2f7bc66a5d7e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change between MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 and 4.1.0 regarding test discovery with vstest.console. This is a known change in the MSTest ecosystem - let me explain what happened.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.x, Microsoft introduced the \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" (also known as the \"new test platform\" or \"MSTest runner\"). In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the default was still VSTest compatibility, but in MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the default changed.\n\nSpecifically, in MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the property `EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage` and the test runner defaulted to VSTest. But in MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the default runner switched from VSTest to the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner). This means that `vstest.console` can no longer discover/run the tests because the test assemblies are no longer built as VSTest-compatible by default.\n\n\nThe core issue is that MSTest.Sdk 4.x enables the new testing platform by default and drops the VSTest adapter, so tests built with it won't work with vstest.console anymore. Users can fix this by switching to `dotnet test` instead, setting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` in their project file to restore VSTest compatibility, or adding the VSTest bridge package.","outputTokens":666},"id":"5d6a85cd-af4f-4964-a976-5adb0028c6b7","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:06:22.866Z","parentId":"e0301f99-19df-4206-837f-669139182864"}
